	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Dwedit</b> [ Mon Aug 16, 2010 2:48 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The kind of compression I'm using:
<br />Big 8x8 blocks of 16x16 tiles, then the map that uses them is RLE compressed.  Each 8x8 block is 4 bits per tile, for 32 bytes per block, packed but not compressed, so there's random access to the tiles.  256 of those would be 8K in size.
<br />
<br />I was also thinking of possibly compressing the blocks instead of just packing them, would need some RAM to hold the decompressed blocks, I have 768 bytes that I haven't reserved yet, so that could be 24 blocks per area.  In order to have any benefit, the blocks would need to be significantly less than 32 bytes each.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


